    "body": "<!--\r\n  Thank you for contributing to Neovim!\r\n  If this is your first time, check out https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#pull-requests-prs\r\n  for our PR guidelines.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\nTerminal title was not being set because no status line terminal options were set for wezterm\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nSet default terminal options\r\n\r\nCloses #20706",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39226#discussion_r3109822099"
                },
                "pull_request": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/39226"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/3109822099"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "the comment seems confusing, since `patch_terminfo_bugs` is about patching \"terminfo bugs\", and the `terminfo_set_if_empty` lines you have added are doing that?\r\n\r\nthis `else` condition applies to any terminal that wasn't recognized.",
            "commit_id": "a252c538b5fb4457b690325f383f8ed4c0acc716",
            "created_at": "2026-04-20T10:03:38Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -2182,6 +2182,10 @@ static void patch_terminfo_bugs(TUIData *tui, const char *term, const char *colo\n     terminfo_set_if_empty(tui, kTerm_enter_italics_mode, \"\\x1b[3m\");\n   } else if (st) {\n     // No bugs in the vanilla terminfo for our purposes.\n+  } else {\n+    // if we have no bugs then we still want title to work\n+    terminfo_set_if_empty(tui, kTerm_to_status_line, \"\\x1b]0;\");\n+    terminfo_set_if_empty(tui, kTerm_from_status_line, \"\\x07\");",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39226#discussion_r3109822099",
            "id": 3109822099,
            "line": 2188,
            "node_id": "PRRC_kwDOAPphoM65XB6T",
