    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "the `else` that you added here applies to any terminal that wasn't recognized.\r\n\r\ndoes wezterm usually set `TERM` to a value that indicates \"wezterm\", so we can use `terminfo_is_term_family` to detect it?\r\n\r\nwe do have some detection for wezterm here: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/515300674733d8337a180dc6468c5f17efe465e1/src/nvim/tui/tui.c#L428-L438\r\n\r\nbut that uses `TERM_PROGRAM` which usually isn't available over ssh (nor all platforms?)\r\n\r\nanyway, it seems like that should at least be passed to `patch_terminfo_bugs` so it can check it if found? that doesn't necessarily solve the problem for all cases, so it may still make sense to add the catch-all `else` that you have added (but i haven't thought through the implications of that, have you?)",
            "created_at": "2026-04-20T10:09:53Z",
